===> TOPIC: De-Lurking, with appreciation

From: Monica Holbrook
mailto:mmi_tech@yahoo.com?CC=ihelpdesk@adventive.com&subject=Thanks


Hello Help-Desk Members,

I have been a lurker and occasional participant in this list since
1996/7, during this time I have started, designed and sold an online
store, started and continue to run a web design/services business
and have developed an increasing interest in the research and
information profession. This last year has been a trying one, partly
due to circumstances beyond my control and partly due to bad choices
(thats the worst - when you know bad times could have been
prevented! Ah the would've-s and could've-s and should've-s of
life..)

As I reflect on the last year and the years before and the year to
come it occurred to me how much this list has helped me over the
years.

I believe it was Martha Retallick who was expressing some discontent
and frustration at helping others and not receiving thank yous.
Well, she's right, it is high time a strong thank you should be
expressed to those who I've found particularly inspirational and I'm
sure there are many of you out there who will agree.

Thank you for:

William Bontrager http://www.willmaster.com
Your never-ending advice and wisdom on cgi-scripts.
Your scripts are affordable (many free) and they work, are easy to
set up and when it can't be figured out you are there to help.
Congratulations on living your dream and working from a mobile home
office.....you are proof that it can happen! (for those of you not
familiar with his story visit his site for more info)

Shel Horowitz http://www.frugalmarketing.com
Your wisdom and down-to-earth reflections on marketing, pr, and
customer relations. You remind us how possible it is with hard work
and good old fashioned creativity to have the life you want. The
autographed copies of your books will always have an honored place
on my bookshelf. Your frugal marketing and frugal fun e-newsletters
are always read and remembered.

Mary Ihla http://www.ihla.com/
Participating so freely and becoming such a valuable resource to the
Internet community. Back in 1996 you started a community website and
in your discovery of the process and intricacies of design, education
and political mediation, I learned too.

Azriela Jaffe http://www.createyourownluck.com
Sharing your life with us all. I learn from your light, conversational
articles. You balance husband, family and a growing business, plus one
of the best newsletters out there today - 'Create Your Own Luck'.
There have been some really down times for me in the last couple of years,
your newsletter always reminds me of the luck in every situation, and
has inspired me to act when I might otherwise have simply just cried ;).

Martha Retallick http://www.lrpdesigns.com
Sharing your increasing knowledge on the web design business. Your
reviews are indepth and on-target. You've expanded your business and
grown into an expert on postcard marketing right before our eyes.
You remind me that the business marketplace is ever-changing and
success if not here already, is just around the corner.

Nancy Roebke http://www.profnet.com
Your wise advice about networking, your fight for intellectual property
rights, for educating us on how to communicate with each other and our
customers. Your articles are engaging and I always walk away a better
business person for having read them.

And of course! Thank you to Eva Rosenberg for
mediating, hosting and always being there.

What can we all learn from these leaders in our community?

Consistency, Dedication, Good Will and Optimism.......Pay Off!
They define success with their achievements and my goal next year
is to capitalize on what I've learned and do the same.

Happy New Year,

Monica Holbrook
Web Designer.....http://www.nutshelldesigninc.com
Nutshell Design, Inc.    web | logo | print
http://www.nutshelldesigninc.com

