=== RESPONSES - NEW ===

===> TOPIC:  SPAM

From: Lynn <lynn@ecgincc.com>

Hi Everyone,

Happy New Year, and I hope you all had great holidays.

I received a piece of mail the other day that was very creative.
Someone forwarded a piece of mail that appeared to be a spam
complaint to me about me. From the mail:

I have received the following unsolicited e-mail from someone at
your domain or your IP range.

I do not wish to receive such messages in the future, so please take
the appropriate measures to ensure that this unsolicited e-mail is
not repeated.

I did some investigating on my own and with UU Net  Security as he
forwarded spam headers did not show anything connected to me - not
my domain, not an IP, mail server, nothing.

This is spam. It is a new trick from spammers. I would expect to see
it more in the future. It was first seen Jan 4 2003, the same day I
received it. Treat it as any other piece of spam.

If anyone want to see the original, please email and I'll be very
happy to forward it.

Lynn Bernstein
ECG Consulting
www.ecg-incc.com

Comment?  mailto:ihelpdesk@adventive.com


